Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: The Vice Presidency and a Precaution Against Death
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00sx758
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 9 Mar 2001
Alistair Cooke considers the health of the American vice-president, Dick Cheney, and wonders whether the Senate could pass President Bush's tax bill and make it law.